// Calculate first insurance: 10% assessment surcharge on each item's unmodified base premium
// For components that group into a block, their unmodified base is 25 G per component item.
// However, if the block applies, the block's base premium is 60 G. Let's see:
// "first insurance: 10 % initial assessment surcharge"
// The integration example says:
// "cursed sword: (100 G base + 50 G curse + 10 G first insurance = 160 G + 5 G fee = 165 G)" -> first insurance is 10 G (10% of 100 G)
// "cursed sword with enchantment 7: (100 G base + 50 G curse + 30 G high enchantment - 20 G loyalty + 10 G first insurance - 15 G follow-up contract = 155 G + 5 G fee = 160 G)" -> first insurance is 10 G (10% of 100 G base)
// So the first insurance surcharge is exactly 10% of the UNMODIFIED base premium of each item.
// Wait, let's look at 3 runes -> base premium 60 G. Unmodified base premium is 3 * 25 = 75 G if no block applies, but with block it's 60 G.
